<TITLE> Death toll from US tornadoes at 45 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DALLAS, Feb 6 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Forty-five people were killed by by tornadoes and thunderstorms that swept the US South, the US National Weather Service said on Wednesday. "Based on reports from our local offices, the death toll now stands at 45. That is 26 in Tennessee, 13 in Arkansas, one in Alabama and five in Kentucky," said Roger Erickson, a meteorologist with the southern regional headquarters for the National Weather Service in Fort Worth.
